This is the kind of links we use with WebSVN uses to compare two paths:

{code}
https://myhost.com/websvn/comp.php?repname=test&compare[]=/@858&compare[]=/@857
{code}

The wiki renderer doesn't handle this correctly, likely because it sees again a '[' character before a ']' character

{code}
[https://myhost.com/websvn/comp.php?repname=test&compare[]=/@858&compare[]=/@857]
[changes|https://myhost.com/websvn/comp.php?repname=test&compare[]=/@858&compare[]=/@857]
{code}

currently displays exactly like that:
[https://myhost.com/websvn/comp.php?repname=test&compare[]=/@858&compare[]=/@857]
[changes|https://myhost.com/websvn/comp.php?repname=test&compare[]=/@858&compare[]=/@857]

