When users upgrade JIRA to 4.2 or later version with XML backup and used a custom directory for attachment path before, as a part of upgrading process JIRA will ask user to choose between using this custom directory or the default directory for attachment path location. 

We observed the scenario that if user has a big JIRA instance, they may run into a trouble when importing XML backup through proxy. The story is that since XML file is big, parsing XML may spend quite a while, and because getting attachment path depends on XML parse, when the "choose path" query is responsed, the client web connection may have been cut off by proxy timeout, then "choose path" query will never be able to send to client side, and it makes restore get to a dead end.

