If a customer adds a table (or view) to the JIRA database (either manually to faciliate SQL reporting or via some kind of plugin) then ofbiz freaks out on every startup and logs a warning. There is maybe some *slight* supportability help from that (though I'm dubious) but it seems like the customer-freak-out-factor outweighs any possible gain. Why does ofbiz even care if I've created another table? I'm not affecting ofbiz and ofbiz isn't affecting me.

I think we should change that statement to info or debug.

